    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Right now with using Spring-Boot 2.0.4 - { } won't work.</p>\n\n<pre><code>@RequestMapping\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>still has String[] as a value parameter, so declaration looks like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code> @RequestMapping(value=[\"/\",\"/index\",\"/login\",\"/home\"], method = RequestMethod.GET)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>** Update - Works With Spring-Boot 2.2**</p>\n\n<pre><code> @RequestMapping(value={\"/\",\"/index\",\"/login\",\"/home\"}, method = RequestMethod.GET)\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1421177,
      "reputation" : 443,
      "user_id" : 1345734,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8a140e0340ec77f79824182072d64da6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "CQLI",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1345734/cqli"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1555482040,
    "creation_date" : 1555482040,
    "answer_id" : 55721106,
    "question_id" : 2513031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>It's better to use PathVariable annotation if you still want to get the uri which was called.</p>\n\n<pre><code>@PostMapping(\"/pub/{action:a|b|c}\")\npublic JSONObject handlexxx(@PathVariable String action, @RequestBody String reqStr){\n...\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or parse it from request object.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4439251,
      "reputation" : 1625,
      "user_id" : 3614215,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/4CsVu.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Marco",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3614215/marco"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 12,
    "last_activity_date" : 1567062830,
    "creation_date" : 1567062830,
    "answer_id" : 57704894,
    "question_id" : 2513031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The shortest way is: <code>@RequestMapping({\"\", \"/\", \"welcome\"})</code></p>\n\n<p>Although you can also do:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>@RequestMapping(value={\"\", \"/\", \"welcome\"})</code></li>\n<li><code>@RequestMapping(path={\"\", \"/\", \"welcome\"})</code></li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1592127,
      "reputation" : 19078,
      "user_id" : 1475228,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 84,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/TgQ5O.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Pritam Banerjee",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1475228/pritam-banerjee"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1584567243,
    "creation_date" : 1584567243,
    "answer_id" : 60747805,
    "question_id" : 2513031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The following is acceptable as well:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@GetMapping(path = { \"/{pathVariable1}/{pathVariable1}/somePath\", \n                     \"/fixedPath/{some-name}/{some-id}/fixed\" }, \n            produces = \"application/json\")\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Same can be applied to <code>@RequestMapping</code> as well</p>\n"
  } ],
